*   **Highway Merging:** Bots will route over existing allied conveyors with a movement cost of 1. Because they always point their newly built conveyors backward to where they came from, any branch built off an existing highway will naturally flow perfectly back into the core.
*   **BFS Network Discovery:** The Core will use a lightning-fast Breadth-First Search (BFS) to trace our physical conveyor network every time a bot needs a job. It will automatically skip any ore that is already connected, inherently handling repairs and preventing redundant targeting.
*   **Job Board Markers:** When a bot selects an ore, it drops a marker at the Core containing the coordinates. Other bots will read these active markers and pick different ores, ensuring perfect spatial distribution.
*   **Greedy A* Optimization:** Using a weighted Chebyshev heuristic ensures the pathfinding finishes within the 2ms limit.
*   **Passive Core Defence:** The core will dynamically manage bot population limits based on the round number and will deploy Sentinel turrets around itself if our economy is booming.

