The bots aggressively claim ore deposits, but only reserve a tiny fraction of Titanium (`harv_cost + 15`) before building a Harvester. When multiple bots build Harvesters simultaneously, they completely drain the global Titanium pool. As a result, when they transition to the `"RETURN"` state to build the conveyor chains back to the core, they encounter a `ti < conv_cost` constraint. The bots freeze in place waiting for Titanium, but because the harvesters aren't connected to the core, the team's Titanium income is precisely **zero**. The entire economy permanently deadlocks, which is why your bot stopped at ~300 Ti in every match while the opponent scaled to 18,000+ Ti.

